---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<BaseLayout title="Missional by Design">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-label">Tobias Treppmann · Oratio&Co</div>
    <h1>Missional<br/>by Design.</h1>
    <p class="hero-subtitle">
      Strategic design, theological reflection, and ministry innovation — for churches, startups, and the teams
      building technology that serves human flourishing.
    </p>
    <div style="margin-top: 2.5rem; display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
      <a href={`${base}/ministry-model-canvas`} class="button">Ministry Model Canvas</a>
      <a href={`${base}/framework`} class="button" style="background: transparent; color: var(--color-white); border: 1px solid var(--color-white);">Product Design Framework</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Thesis -->
  <section class="section section-cream">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="max-width: 70ch;">
        <div style="font-size: 0.8rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-weight: 700; opacity: 0.6;">The Thesis</div>
        <h2>All ministry<br/>is designed.</h2>
        <p class="lead" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
          "All ministry is designed — whether you know it or not." — <em>Tyler Prieb, Missional Labs</em>
        </p>
        <p class="lead">
          In rapidly changing contexts, faithful witness requires continual re-contextualization. Churches and ministry
          teams need the same strategic muscles that startups have developed over the last two decades: cultural
          exegesis, rapid iteration, user-centered thinking, honest measurement.
        </p>
        <p class="lead">
          <strong>Missional by Design</strong> is a body of work that adapts these tools — rigorously and theologically — for ministry.
          It includes strategic frameworks for churches, principles for building digital tools that serve formation, and
          consulting for teams working at the intersection of faith, design, and technology.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Three Pillars -->
  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="margin-bottom: 4rem; max-width: 60ch;">
        <div style="font-size: 0.8rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-weight: 700; opacity: 0.6;">The Work</div>
        <h2>Three tools.<br/>One approach.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-3">
        <a href={`${base}/ministry-model-canvas`} class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-card-num">01</div>
          <h3>Ministry Model Canvas</h3>
          <p>
            A nine-block strategic planning framework for churches and ministries — adapted from the Business Model
            Canvas to help teams clarify their target, name their good news, and design toward missional effectiveness.
          </p>
          <div class="pillar-card-link">Explore the canvas →</div>
        </a>

        <a href={`${base}/framework`} class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-card-num">02</div>
          <h3>Missional Product Design</h3>
          <p>
            Nine principles and six diagnostic questions for building digital tools that serve spiritual formation —
            resisting engagement optimization in favor of human flourishing. Drawn from 195+ sources across theology,
            behavioral science, and product design.
          </p>
          <div class="pillar-card-link">Read the framework →</div>
        </a>

        <a href={`${base}/blog`} class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-card-num">03</div>
          <h3>Writing</h3>
          <p>
            Essays on missional design, digital formation, ministry innovation, and the surprising overlap between
            churches and startups. Thought leadership from the field, not the seminar room.
          </p>
          <div class="pillar-card-link">Read the essays →</div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Manifesto - specifically scoped to product design now -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="margin-bottom: 3rem; max-width: 70ch;">
        <div style="font-size: 0.8rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-weight: 700; opacity: 0.6;">The Manifesto · Product Design</div>
        <h2>Four values<br/>we choose first.</h2>
        <p class="lead" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
          When building technology for spiritual formation, we have learned that what serves formation also produces
          better products. While the items on the right sustain businesses and serve users, we choose the items on
          the left first when the two conflict.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="manifesto-values">
        <div class="left">Formation</div>
        <div class="sep">over</div>
        <div class="right">Engagement</div>

        <div class="left">Partnership</div>
        <div class="sep">over</div>
        <div class="right">Persuasion</div>

        <div class="left">Challenge</div>
        <div class="sep">over</div>
        <div class="right">Comfort</div>

        <div class="left">Community</div>
        <div class="sep">over</div>
        <div class="right">Platform</div>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top: 3rem;">
        <a href={`${base}/framework`} class="button">Read the full framework</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Work with us / services -->
  <section class="section section-ink">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="margin-bottom: 3rem; max-width: 60ch;">
        <div style="font-size: 0.8rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-weight: 700; opacity: 0.6;">Work With Us</div>
        <h2>For teams<br/>putting it into practice.</h2>
        <p class="lead" style="margin-top: 2rem; opacity: 0.9;">
          Consulting, facilitation, and training for churches, ministries, and faith-driven teams building new things.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-3">
        <div style="padding: 2rem; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2);">
          <div style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 900; font-size: 0.8rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 1rem; opacity: 0.7;">01 · Consultation</div>
          <h4>Ministry Consultation</h4>
          <p>Personalized consultation to help your ministry navigate the challenges of building effective, faithful technology and ministry models in the 21st century.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="padding: 2rem; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2);">
          <div style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 900; font-size: 0.8rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 1rem; opacity: 0.7;">02 · Training</div>
          <h4>Innovation Training</h4>
          <p>Equipping your team with the skills and frameworks to implement formation-centered strategies — workshops on the canvas, the framework, and applied design thinking for ministry.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="padding: 2rem; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2);">
          <div style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 900; font-size: 0.8rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 1rem; opacity: 0.7;">03 · Cohort</div>
          <h4>Online Ministry Innovation Cohort</h4>
          <p>Join a community of practitioners working at the intersection of faith, design, and technology — sharing experience and learning together.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top: 3rem;">
        <a href="mailto:hello@treppmann.design" class="button">Get in touch</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .pillar-card {
    display: block;
    padding: 2.5rem;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
    color: var(--color-white);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all var(--transition);
    position: relative;
  }

  .pillar-card:hover {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .pillar-card-num {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 900;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  .pillar-card h3 {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .pillar-card p {
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.5;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .pillar-card-link {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 900;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
</style>
